<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n34034a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34034a">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34034a"> 34(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> rule of signs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Rule of Signs</b>. The product of two terms with like signs is positive; the product of two terms with unlike signs is negative. <small> Hall &amp; Knight, <a name="HSHK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HSHK"><cite title="source">Elementary Algebra for Schools</cite></a> (n.d) 28</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: In multiplication by a negative quantity, when the multiplier is negative we first multipy by its absolute value, and then change the sign of the resulting product. Thus, 3&times;(-4) = -(3&times;4) = -12. So (-3)&times;(-4) = 3&times;4. </mm> </dd></dl>
